Pre checks/tasks:
Check for free space in /var and /tmp folders
Check for compapability for db and application regarding the new packets that will be installed


Open ticket describing the change, goals and date
Present the change on TAB/CAB meeting
Arrange resourses from DB team and from Application team on the date



On the date of change:
Create snapshot/back up of the system
Ask DB team to shutdown DB and wait for confirmation.
After confirmation ask Application team to shutdown the running applications.
After getting confirmation  perform yum update -y
Reboot the system
After the reboot check if new kernel is installed, all services are started and all mount points are mounted accordingly to /etc/fstab
Ask for DB team start their databases
Ask for application for start their application and check if everything is ok
Contact the customer for confirmation if everything is ok
